/**
 * üß© ABSTRACT CLASS vs INTERFACE ‚Äî WITH MINI EXAMPLES
 * ---------------------------------------------------
 *
 * | Feature / Concept | ABSTRACT CLASS | INTERFACE |
 * |-------------------|----------------|------------|
 *
 * 1Ô∏è‚É£ **Purpose**
 * - Used to share common logic among related classes.
 *   üß† Example:
 *       abstract class Animal { void eat() { } }
 * - Defines a contract/behavior that can be applied to any class.
 *   üß† Example:
 *       interface Flyable { void fly(); }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 2Ô∏è‚É£ **Keyword Used**
 *   abstract class Animal { }
 *   interface Flyable { }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 3Ô∏è‚É£ **Methods**
 * - Abstract + Concrete allowed:
 *       abstract class Shape {
 *           abstract void draw();
 *           void color() { System.out.println("Color added"); }
 *       }
 * - Interface methods abstract by default:
 *       interface Drawable { void draw(); }
 * - Since Java 8 ‚Üí can also have:
 *       default void fill() { }
 *       static void info() { }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 4Ô∏è‚É£ **Variables / Fields**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí can have normal variables:
 *       abstract class Bird { int wings = 2; }
 * - Interface ‚Üí variables are public static final:
 *       interface Planet { double GRAVITY = 9.8; }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 5Ô∏è‚É£ **Constructors**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí ‚úÖ can have constructors:
 *       abstract class Car { Car() { System.out.println("Car base"); } }
 * - Interface ‚Üí ‚ùå cannot have constructors:
 *       interface Machine { } // no constructor allowed
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 6Ô∏è‚É£ **Access Modifiers**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí can use public, private, protected:
 *       protected void sound() { }
 * - Interface ‚Üí all methods implicitly public:
 *       void start(); // same as public abstract void start();
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 7Ô∏è‚É£ **Multiple Inheritance**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí ‚ùå Only one can be extended:
 *       class Dog extends Animal { }
 * - Interface ‚Üí ‚úÖ multiple interfaces can be implemented:
 *       class Robot implements Flyable, Runnable { }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 8Ô∏è‚É£ **Relationship Type**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí "IS-A" relationship.
 *       Dog IS-A Animal
 * - Interface ‚Üí "CAN-DO" relationship.
 *       Bird CAN-DO Flyable
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 9Ô∏è‚É£ **State / Data**
 * - Abstract class can have state (fields with values):
 *       abstract class Employee { String name; }
 * - Interface cannot have state (only constants):
 *       interface Config { int VERSION = 1; }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * üîü **When to Use**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí when classes are closely related.
 *       abstract class Vehicle { void move() { } }
 * - Interface ‚Üí when behavior applies to many unrelated classes.
 *       interface Payable { void pay(); }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ **Default / Static Methods**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí normal methods allowed.
 *       void brake() { System.out.println("Braking..."); }
 * - Interface ‚Üí since Java 8:
 *       default void stop() { }
 *       static void info() { }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ **Extends / Implements**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí extended by a class:
 *       class Dog extends Animal { }
 * - Interface ‚Üí implemented by a class:
 *       class Plane implements Flyable { }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ **Multiple Implementation**
 * - Class can extend only one abstract class:
 *       class Car extends Vehicle { }
 * - Class can implement many interfaces:
 *       class Drone implements Flyable, Recordable { }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ **_1_Primitive Method**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí can have main method ‚úÖ
 *       abstract class Demo { public static void main(...) { } }
 * - Interface ‚Üí since Java 8, can have static main ‚úÖ (rarely used)
 *       interface Demo { static void main(...) { } }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * 1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ **Example Use Case**
 * - Abstract class ‚Üí base class with common logic:
 *       abstract class Shape { abstract double area(); }
 * - Interface ‚Üí behavior capability:
 *       interface Drawable { void draw(); }
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------
 * üß† QUICK MEMORY TRICK:
 * "Use ABSTRACT CLASS for FAMILY (shared logic),
 *  INTERFACE for ABILITIES (shared behavior)."
 *
 * üê∂ Example:
 *   class Dog extends Animal implements Flyable, Runnable { }
 *
 */
